snippet.textDisplay: Am I the only one who didnt see Wilder's excuse as that bad? I am not a Wilder fan by any degree. Don't even like the guy. Im British and I was so happy Tyson won. But I also was wondering why Wilder looked like Bambi on ice in the first round. First thing I said to my dad was: "Is there something wrong with his legs? He looks wombly." People were saying it was obvious from the second round but it looked remarkably clear to me even from round 1.  And I found it interesting to hear what the reason was. I thought it was refreshing to hear a boxer tell us what happened rather than Joshua (who Im a big fan of) saying nothing and leaving people to speculate for months when there was clearly something wrong. Yes, Wilder got beat by the better man that night and yes, the excuse was pathetic. But Im glad we know what happened and now we can laugh at him for it. The costume was ridiculous imo.
